{"tree":{"type":"node","kind":"SOURCE_FILE","width":26,"children":[{"type":"node","kind":"LET_BINDING","width":17,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"let","width":3},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"ERROR","width":4,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"open","width":4}]},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"CONSTRUCTOR_PATTERN","width":5,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"List","width":4},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1}]},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"in","width":2},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":"\n","width":1}]},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"ERROR","width":3,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"map","width":3}]},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"ERROR","width":1,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"f","width":1}]},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":"\n","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"ERROR","width":2,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"xs","width":2}]}]},"diagnostics":[{"kind":{"id":"E0007","name":"invalid-pattern","expected":"identifier or pattern","found":{"kind":"keyword","text":"open"},"fix":"use a different name like open_","hint":"\nThe left side of a let-expression allows you to pattern match on values to assign them to variables, but also to deconstruct them and access their inner values.\n\n   ```ocaml\n   let variable = 42 in\n   let { x; _ } = point in\n   let Some x = optional in\n   (* ... *)\n   ```\n\nBeware that pattern matching on only one of many possible values will lead to runtime errors!\n"},"span":{"start":8,"end":9}},{"kind":{"id":"E0003","name":"missing-let-binding-equals","expected":"=","found":{"kind":"keyword","text":"in"},"fix":"add = between the pattern and expression","hint":"Every let binding needs an = between the pattern and the expression."},"span":{"start":13,"end":13}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"identifier","text":"map"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":20,"end":21}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"identifier","text":"f"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":22,"end":23}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"identifier","text":"xs"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":25,"end":26}}]}
